From: David Rudolph <bowmq1@netzero.net>
Date: Sun, 14 Sep 2003 02:45:44 GMT
Subject: Bubonic - Plague

I just returned from southeast Montana near the town of Broadus. The Praire
Dog Towns are empty due to the bubonic plague.
---
David Rudolph
<bowmq1@netzero.net>
[Further information has been requested from Montana. - Mod.MHJ]
[Broadus is located in the southeast of Montana, whereas the deer mule
found positive for plague (see: Plague, mule deer - USA (MT) 20030911.2286)
was located in the southwest of Montana. - Mod.MPP]
